abstract: France's competition watchdog fined Google 150 million euros ($167 million) on Friday for abusing its power over the treatment of advertisers, saying it applied opaque rules and changed them at will.
snippet: France's competition watchdog fined Google 150 million euros ($167 million) on Friday for abusing its power over the treatment of advertisers, saying it applied opaque rules and changed them at will.
lead_paragraph: PARIS — France's competition watchdog fined Google 150 million euros ($167 million) on Friday for abusing its power over the treatment of advertisers, saying it applied opaque rules and changed them at will.
headline_main: France Fines Google 150 Million Euros for Opaque Advertising Rules
headline_print_headline: France Fines Google 150 Million Euros for Opaque Advertising Rules

abstract: President Donald Trump announced on Thursday that a Democratic U.S. lawmaker who opposed his party's move to impeach the Republican president was switching parties, a day after the House of Representatives approved articles of impeachment.
snippet: President Donald Trump announced on Thursday that a Democratic U.S. lawmaker who opposed his party's move to impeach the Republican president was switching parties, a day after the House of Representatives approved articles of impeachment.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump announced on Thursday that a Democratic U.S. lawmaker who opposed his party's move to impeach the Republican president was switching parties, a day after the House of Representatives approved articles of impeachment.
headline_main: Trump Announces Democrat Van Drew Switching to Republican Party
headline_print_headline: Trump Announces Democrat Van Drew Switching to Republican Party

abstract: President Donald Trump said on Thursday he wants an immediate trial in the Senate, after House Speaker Nancy Pelosi said she would not hand off impeachment to the Senate until she learned how Republicans would manage the proceeding.
snippet: President Donald Trump said on Thursday he wants an immediate trial in the Senate, after House Speaker Nancy Pelosi said she would not hand off impeachment to the Senate until she learned how Republicans would manage the proceeding.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump said on Thursday he wants an immediate trial in the Senate, after House Speaker Nancy Pelosi said she would not hand off impeachment to the Senate until she learned how Republicans would manage the proceeding.
headline_main: Trump Says He Wants an 'Immediate' Senate Impeachment Trial
headline_print_headline: Trump Says He Wants an 'Immediate' Senate Impeachment Trial

abstract: Germany's defense minister signed an agreement Friday with the country's main Jewish organization to reintroduce military rabbis, saying it was a “strong sign” of the importance of Jewish life in the country.
snippet: Germany's defense minister signed an agreement Friday with the country's main Jewish organization to reintroduce military rabbis, saying it was a “strong sign” of the importance of Jewish life in the country.
lead_paragraph: BERLIN — Germany's defense minister signed an agreement Friday with the country's main Jewish organization to reintroduce military rabbis, saying it was a “strong sign” of the importance of Jewish life in the country.
headline_main: Germany Signs 'Historic' Deal to Reintroduce Military Rabbis
headline_print_headline: Germany Signs 'Historic' Deal to Reintroduce Military Rabbis

abstract: Russian investigators on Friday named the man who opened fire on the headquarters of the FSB security service in Moscow as Yevgeny Manyurov, a 39-year-old former security guard from just outside the capital.
snippet: Russian investigators on Friday named the man who opened fire on the headquarters of the FSB security service in Moscow as Yevgeny Manyurov, a 39-year-old former security guard from just outside the capital.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — Russian investigators on Friday named the man who opened fire on the headquarters of the FSB security service in Moscow as Yevgeny Manyurov, a 39-year-old former security guard from just outside the capital.
headline_main: Russia Names Gunman Behind Moscow Shooting, Death Toll Rises to Two
headline_print_headline: Russia Names Gunman Behind Moscow Shooting, Death Toll Rises to Two

abstract: Kazakhstan will drop a requirement for public protests to be approved by authorities, make it easier to form political parties, and reduce punishments for hate speech and libel, President Kassym-Jomart Tokayev said on Friday.
snippet: Kazakhstan will drop a requirement for public protests to be approved by authorities, make it easier to form political parties, and reduce punishments for hate speech and libel, President Kassym-Jomart Tokayev said on Friday.
lead_paragraph: NUR-SULTAN — Kazakhstan will drop a requirement for public protests to be approved by authorities, make it easier to form political parties, and reduce punishments for hate speech and libel, President Kassym-Jomart Tokayev said on Friday.
headline_main: Kazakhstan to Liberalize Rules on Protests and Political Parties
headline_print_headline: Kazakhstan to Liberalize Rules on Protests and Political Parties

abstract: Dozens of Rohingya Muslims including children wept in a Myanmar court on Friday as they were brought in to face charges of illegally traveling without proper documents.
snippet: Dozens of Rohingya Muslims including children wept in a Myanmar court on Friday as they were brought in to face charges of illegally traveling without proper documents.
lead_paragraph: PATHEIN, Myanmar — Dozens of Rohingya Muslims including children wept in a Myanmar court on Friday as they were brought in to face charges of illegally traveling without proper documents.
headline_main: Rohingya Weep in Myanmar Court as They Face Charge of Illegal Travel
headline_print_headline: Rohingya Weep in Myanmar Court as They Face Charge of Illegal Travel

abstract: Six people died and dozens were injured on Friday as Indian police clashed with thousands of protesters who again took to the streets in several parts of the country to oppose a new law they say discriminates against Muslims.
snippet: Six people died and dozens were injured on Friday as Indian police clashed with thousands of protesters who again took to the streets in several parts of the country to oppose a new law they say discriminates against Muslims.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI/LUCKNOW — Six people died and dozens were injured on Friday as Indian police clashed with thousands of protesters who again took to the streets in several parts of the country to oppose a new law they say discriminates against Muslims.
headline_main: Six Dead in Deadliest Day of Indian Citizenship Law Protests
headline_print_headline: Six Dead in Deadliest Day of Indian Citizenship Law Protests

abstract: Turkish authorities on Friday detained a mayor from the pro-Kurdish Peoples' Democratic Party (HDP) due to suspected links to Kurdish militants, a security source said, the latest in a crackdown on mayors from the party since elections this year.
snippet: Turkish authorities on Friday detained a mayor from the pro-Kurdish Peoples' Democratic Party (HDP) due to suspected links to Kurdish militants, a security source said, the latest in a crackdown on mayors from the party since elections this year.
lead_paragraph: ISTANBUL — Turkish authorities on Friday detained a mayor from the pro-Kurdish Peoples' Democratic Party (HDP) due to suspected links to Kurdish militants, a security source said, the latest in a crackdown on mayors from the party since elections this year.
headline_main: Turkey Detains Pro-Kurdish Mayor on Suspected Terrorism Links
headline_print_headline: Turkey Detains Pro-Kurdish Mayor on Suspected Terrorism Links
